== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1606]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|ja|南部重直|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[1664]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1735]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kangen]] 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1200]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Confucian scholar from the Southern Song, regarded as the founder of Zhu Xi's school of Confucianism (birth year unknown, died [[1130]]). * [[Genki]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1571]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tsukahara Bokuden|ja|塚原卜伝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a master of Kenjutsu (died [[1489]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1634]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|ja|初代大橋宗桂|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a shogi master and the first Meijin (died [[1555]]).
