{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 9''' is the 9th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1211]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Shōgen|ja|承元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1847]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A scholarly institute for the court nobles was established in front of the Imperial Palace's Kenshun-mon in Kyoto, which is regarded as the origin of the {{ill|Gakushūin|ja|学習院|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1851]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued the Kabunakama Saikōrei. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1856]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The practice of the "fumi-e" (stepping on images) at the port cities of Nagasaki, Shimoda, and other open ports was abolished. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, appealing for submission and apology to save the Tokugawa family. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The soldiers protecting the emperor, numbering 10,000 from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains, were re-designated as the Konoei.
