== Events == * {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1211]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Shōgen|ja|承元}} to {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦}}. * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1847]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日}}) – A scholarly institute for the court nobles was established in front of the Imperial Palace's Kenshun-mon in Kyoto, which is regarded as the origin of the {{ill|Gakushūin|ja|学習院}}. * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1851]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued the Kabunakama Saikōrei. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1856]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日}}) – The practice of the "fumi-e" (stepping on images) at the port cities of Nagasaki, Shimoda, and other open ports was abolished. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日}}) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛}}, appealing for submission and apology to save the Tokugawa family. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日}}) – The soldiers protecting the emperor, numbering 10,000 from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains, were re-designated as the Konoei.
== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1606]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|ja|南部重直}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[1664]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1735]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kangen]] 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1200]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日}}) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子}}, a Confucian scholar from the Southern Song, regarded as the founder of Zhu Xi's school of Confucianism (birth year unknown, died [[1130]]). * [[Genki]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1571]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日}}) – {{ill|Tsukahara Bokuden|ja|塚原卜伝}}, a master of Kenjutsu (died [[1489]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1634]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日}}) – {{ill|Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|ja|初代大橋宗桂}}, a shogi master and the first Meijin (died [[1555]]).
