== Events == * {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1211]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|qq=}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Shōgen|ja|承元|qq=}} to {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦|qq=}}. * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|qq=}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1847]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|qq=}}) – A scholarly institute for the court nobles was established in front of the Imperial Palace's Kenshun-mon in Kyoto, which is regarded as the origin of the {{ill|Gakushūin|ja|学習院|qq=}}. * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|qq=}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1851]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|qq=}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued the Kabunakama Saikōrei. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1856]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|qq=}}) – The practice of the "fumi-e" (stepping on images) at the port cities of Nagasaki, Shimoda, and other open ports was abolished. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|qq=}}) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with {{ill|Saigō Ta