* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, appealing for submission and apology to save the Tokugawa family.
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The soldiers protecting the emperor, numbering 10,000 from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains, were re-designated as the Konoei.

== Births ==
* [[Keichō]] 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1606]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|ja|南部重直|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[1664]]).
* {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1735]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[1808]]).

== Deaths ==
* [[Kangen]] 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1200]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Confucian scholar from the Southern Song, regarded as the founder of Zhu Xi's school of Confucianism (birth year unknown, died [[1130]]).
* [[Genki]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1571]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tsukahara Bokuden|ja|塚原卜伝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a master of Kenjutsu (died [[1489]]).
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1634]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|ja|初代大橋宗桂|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a shogi master and the first Meijin (died [[1555]]).

