gorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, appealing for submission and apology to save the Tokugawa family. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The soldiers protecting the emperor, numbering 10,000 from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains, were re-designated as the Konoei.
