== Events == * [[:en:Kenryaku|Kenryaku]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1211|1211]] [[:en:April 23|April 23]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Jōgen (Kamakura period)|Shōgen]] to [[:en:Kenryaku|Kenryaku]]. * [[:en:Kōka|Kōka]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1847|1847]] [[:en:April 23|April 23]]) – A scholarly institute for the court nobles was established in front of the Imperial Palace's Kenshun-mon in Kyoto, which is regarded as the origin of the {{ill|Gakushūin|ja|学習院|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gakushūin|qq=}}. * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1851|1851]] [[:en:April 10|April 10]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued the Kabunakama Saikōrei. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1856|1856]] [[:en:April 13|April 13]]) – The practice of the "fumi-e" (stepping on images) at the port cities of Nagasaki, Shimoda, and other open ports was abolished. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年}}[[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]] ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – At Shunpū Castle, Yamauchi Yōtoku met with [[:en:Saigō Takamori|Saigō Takamori]], appealing for submission and apology to save the Tokugawa family. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – The soldiers protecting the emperor, numbering 10,000 from the Satsuma, Chōshū, and Tosa domains, were re-designated as the Konoei.
== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1606|1606]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Nanbu Shigenao|Nanbu Shigenao]], the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[:en:1664|1664]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 20th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1735|1735]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katō Chien|qq=}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[:en:1808|1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kangen]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1200|1200]] [[:en:April 23|April 23]]) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhu Xi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 朱熹|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 朱熹}}, a Confucian scholar from the Southern Song, regarded as the founder of Zhu Xi's school of Confucianism (birth year unknown, died [[:en:1130|1130]]). * [[Genki]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1571|1571]] [[:en:April 3|April 3]]) – [[:en:Tsukahara Bokuden|Tsukahara Bokuden]], a master of Kenjutsu (died [[:en:1489|1489]]). * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1634|1634]] [[:en:April 6|April 6]]) – {{ill|Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|ja|初代大橋宗桂|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大橋宗桂 (初代)|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大橋宗桂 (初代)}}, a shogi master and the first Meijin (died [[:en:1555|1555]]).
