== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1606|1606]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Nanbu Shigenao|Nanbu Shigenao]], the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[:en:1664|1664]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 20th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1735|1735]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katō Chien|qq=}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[:en:1808|1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kangen]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1200|1200]] [[:en:April 23|April 23]]) – {{ill|Zhu Xi|ja|朱子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhu Xi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 朱熹|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 朱熹}}, a Confucian scholar from the Southern Song, regarded as the founder of Zhu Xi's school of Confucianism (birth year unknown, died [[:en:1130|1130]]). * [[:en:Genki|Genki]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1571|1571]] [[:en:April 3|April 3]]) – [[:en:Tsukahara Bokuden|Tsukahara Bokuden]], a master of Kenjutsu (died [[:en:1489|1489]]). * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1634|1634]] [[:en:April 6|April 6]]) – {{ill|Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|ja|初代大橋宗桂|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hatsudai Ōhashi Sōketsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大橋宗桂 (初代)|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大橋宗桂 (初代)}}, a shogi master and the first Meijin (died [[:en:1555|1555]]).
